======================================================================
RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN β_4=6 AND Z_7 REPRESENTATION THEORY
======================================================================
  β_4 = 6 = p-1 = number of nontrivial characters of Z_p
  Conjecture: H_{(p-3)/2}(P_p) ≅ regular representation minus trivial

  P_3: m=(3-3)/2=0, β_0=1 (always 1 for β_0)
  P_5: m=(5-3)/2=1, β_1=1 ≠ p-1=4. FAILS!
  P_7: m=(7-3)/2=2, β_2=0 ≠ p-1=6. FAILS!

  Wait — P_7's nonzero β is at m=4, not m=2.
  (p-3)/2 = 2 but β_2 = 0. The nonzero β is at m = p-3 = 4.

  P_3: nonzero β at m=1, value=1. p-3=0, p-2=1
  P_5: nonzero β at m=1, value=1. p-3=2, p-2=3
  P_7: nonzero β at m=4, value=6. p-3=4!

  NEW CONJECTURE: For Paley P_p with p ≡ 3 mod 4:
    If p ≥ 7: β_{p-3} = p-1, all other β_m = 0 for m ≥ 1
    chi(P_p) = 1 + (-1)^{p-3}*(p-1) = 1 + (p-1) = p (since p-3 even)

  Verification:
    P_7: chi = 1 + 6 = 7 = p ✓
    P_3: chi = 0 ≠ 3 (small case exception)
    P_5: chi = 0 ≠ 5 (small case exception)

